      "content": "The long-term consequences, namely the rise of extremist groups and regional chaos, are a devastating indictment of the intervention's overall strategy. When a targeted military action precipitates a decade of instability and empowers terrorist elements, it fundamentally undermines any claim of strategic success. This outcome demonstrates that the intervention was not a clean victory, but rather a costly geopolitical miscalculation with catastrophic secondary effects.",
      "source": "target",
